<p>I have multiple methods with business logic. For example,</p>  <pre><code>@Transactional(isolation = Isolation.REPEATABLE_READ) public Subscription createSimpleSubscription(User user) {     //do business logic     return createSubscription(user, true); }  @Transactional(isolation = Isolation.SERIALIZABLE) public Subscription createSubscription(User user, boolean flag) {     Subscription s = new Subscription;     s.setUser(user);     s.setFlag(flag);     dao.save(s);      return s; } </code></pre>  <p>What happens with isolcation level when I call  createSimpleSubscription(User user) which calls createSubscription(User user, boolean flag) with another isolation level?</p>  <p>Default propogation level is Propagation.REQUIRED. That means when call createSubscription(User user, boolean flag) within method createSimpleSubscription(User user) no new transaction is created.</p>  <p>Please, refer to documentation.</p>